  "text": "Total RNA was extracted from rat myocardial tissue by TRIzol reagent and measured by NANODROP 2000 (Thermo Scientific) [CITATION_1] . Subsequently, reverse-transcription was performed with Prime-Script6 RT Reagent Kit according to manufacturer's instructions. Quantitative PCR was carried out using 7900 Real-Time PCR System (Applied Biosystems, USA). -actin was used as an internal reference. Primer sequences used for the RT-PCR are listed in Table 2 . Proteins were then transferred onto Nitrocellulose Blotting membrane (Life Sciences, Mexico). After blocking with Odyssey5 blocking Buffer (LI-COR, Lincoln USA) for 2h at 37 ∘ C, membranes were incubated with primary antibodies (Collagen I, Collagen III, MMP-2, MMP-9, CD31, -SMA, VE-cadherin, FSP-1, Vimentin, HIF-1 , NRG-1, phosphoErbB2, phospho-ErbB4, p-AKT, snail, -actin) ( Table 3) at 4 ∘ C overnight. After being rinsed with TBST 3 times, the membranes were further incubated with secondary antibodies at 37 ∘ C for 1 hr. Finally, the membranes were being rinsed with TBST 3 times before scanned by Odyssey (LI-COR, Lincoln USA). The -actin was used as a corresponding internal control.",
